Procedure*Text: In this section, you will be presented with a series of objects. Please name as many possible uses for this object as you can think of by typing them in the box below each object.

Please keep in mind that a single object will have more than one use. For example, a ball can be thrown or can be bounced or even stepped on. When listing multiple uses for one object, please separate each use with a comma (i.e., thrown, bounced, stepped on)
Before starting the experiment, you will complete a short practice sesstion. Press ENTER when you are ready to begin.
Please name all of the ways you could use this object. Keep in mind that one object can have many uses. Separate your responses with a comma.
Response*JOL: you could fill it out, shred it, burn it, take each shredded piece and tape it to the wall, take each piece and use it as confetti at a wedding, you could use it to fold origami, you could use it as very uncomfortable toilet paper, you could stack it up to reach something, you could make a paper airplane and throw it at someones eye, you could tape them together to make one huge sheet and use it as a parachute, you could make it into clothing, you could make it into a blanket, you could run it over with your car, you could make flowers and chain them together, you could make a wreath, you could draw on the pieces, you could cut out each word or letter and rearrange it all to make poetry or a story
